 Shey

 Based on an English play by Susan Hill, Shey is a suspense thriller dished out with a dash of the supernatural. Set in the marshlands of the British east coast, the play centres around a mysterious young woman and a solicitor who tries to unravel her past. Presented by Theatron . 

 Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm, on January 14

 Nirnoy

 The production by Chetana is an adaptation of David Auburn?s Proof. With a mathematical genius and his daughter in focus, Nirnoy traces the thin line dividing creative genius and eccentricity. Directed by Arun Mukhopadhyay.

 Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 6.30 pm, January 17

 Rangayatra

 The 30th anniversary celebrations of Rangakarmee will be wrapped up with an evening of song and dance. The line-up features Gambhira and Chhau dance by Midnapore artistes, music and dance by Nageen Tanvir (choreography by Suman Saraogi), a Naya Theatre play Tambaku Ke Nuksanat enacted by Habib Tanvir, and theatre songs by Rangakarmee.

 Catch it on the Rabindra Sadan campus, 4 pm onwards, on January 18




